DESCRIPTION

   The Bob Shop is a Sprite/Bob editor written in Amos Pro V:2.0.
   It is a paint program designed specifically around the creation of
   sprites/bobs for use in games and animations with an emphasis
   on creating animated sequences.

FEATURES

   -Full set of drawing tools line, free hand, curve, fill, polygon,
    rectangle, circle and ellipse.
   -Four built in brush shapes plus the ability to clip custom brushes
    from any area of the screen.
   -Registered version can be run directly from the Amos editor as an
    accessory.
   -Page flipping allows you to interactively compare previous frames
    to current frame while drawing.
   -Play animated sequences using VCR type controls.
   -Variable zoom.
   -Hot Spot placement.
   -Pattern fills.
   -Demo version is time limited to 15 minutes.

SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS

   -Amos 1.3 or 2.0 (must have 2.0 to run as accessory)
   -1 meg recommended.

HOST

   Aminet FTP sites (ftp.wustl.edu, ftp.luth.se, etc)

